text:
Hey Angelic, HubSpot minifies the css (and js) for you. There’s no need to minify it yourself

Tipp: If you want to get rid of the empty space that’s created by hubl in a rendered css(only in the design manager) you can write your hubl like this:
```{%- set HUBLNAME = SOMETHING -%}

{#- comment -#}

{%- for X in Y -%}

{%- if X -%}
{%- else/elif -%}
{%- ended -%}
```
So just add a „dash/minus“ to it.
